The paper deals with privacy-preserving statistical query processing over sensitive data, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper proposes a new technique for answering batch linear queries with high accuracy under differential privacy, which involves mathematical optimization and machine learning techniques, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also presents experimental results using real data, which falls under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
